history.content: Not sure about the other classes but I took STAT133 last semester and it was pretty much the easiest class I have ever taken. Very low workload and the class is pretty much a very slow intro to programming for those who've never programmed before.

Taking 61C P/NP (have credit from CC, taking it to prepare better for 162) and the rest is letter grade, I did really well in 61A and did alright in Hilfinger's 61B. also already declared. Is this a manageable workload?
history.subject: How doable is 61C + 170 + 188 + STAT 133?
